ning Test Structure**\\n\\nI need to focus on using public classes only while keeping tests with package-private domains. I’m thinking of creating a test called repositoryPersistsUpdatesQueriesAndDeletesAggregate. In this context, I can get JdbcTemplate to execute the creation of a \\\"people\\\" table. \\n\\nHowever, I’ve got to be careful that repository bean creation initializes the mapping before the table is ready. Then, after saving a new Person object, I’ll assert that the ID was assigned. I wonder if querying by name will require a @Query annotation, but I think Spring Data JDBC might support derived queries. This is interesting!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_3ygzrqKrwjL2yGCKFHWyWCPs|fc_0864a54a441f35ff016a0cca41f5c88192902b7048f3a5fbee", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "tmp=$(mktemp -d); cd $tmp; curl -sSLO https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/springframework/boot/spring-boot-data-jdbc/4.0.6/spring-boot-data-jdbc-4.0.6.jar; javap -classpath spring-boot-data-jdbc-4.0.6.jar -private -v org.springframework.boot.data.jdbc.autoconfigure.DataJdbcRepositoriesAutoConfiguration | grep -A120 RuntimeVisibleAnnotations", "timeout": 30}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 662, "output": 815, "cacheRead": 13824, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 15301, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1779223093588, "responseId": "resp_0864a54a441f35ff016a0cca35f7f88192ab11d2653e685b05"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_3ygzrqKrwjL2yGCKFHWyWCPs|fc_0864a54a441f35ff016a0cca41f5c88192902b7048f3a5fbee", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "  #16 = Utf8               RuntimeVisibleAnnotations\n  #17 = Utf8               Lorg/springframework/boot/autoconfigure/AutoConfiguration;\n  #18 = Utf8               after\n  #19 = Utf8               Lorg/springframework/boot/jdbc/autoconfigure/JdbcTemplat