[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring Spring Data JDBC Id Insertion**\n\nI'm looking into how Spring Data JDBC handles default ID insertion. When creating a new entity with a null ID, it uses an insert statement and generates a key if the identity is set. For the name and age fields, I can use the @Column annotation.\n\nFor example, a table setup could look like: `CREATE TABLE people (id BIGINT GENERATED BY DEFAULT AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL, age INTEGER NOT NULL)`. I also need to consider the class structure for the entity and how it manages IDs during save operations.\n\n**Defining a Person Repository**\n\nI'm focusing on creating a repository interface for managing `Person` entities. I'll extend `CrudRepository<Person, Long>` to provide basic CRUD operations. Additionally, I want to define two methods: one for finding persons by their name with `List<Person> findByName(String name)` and another for finding persons older than a certain age with `List<Person> findByAgeGreaterThan(int age)`. I might want to consider whether to return an `Iterable` type as well. Doing this will streamline data retrieval!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0864a54a441f35ff016a0cca791f68819294961dde50029a52\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqDMqNcjx7_kVLIfmQm_LuLj_rfW-1L9Cpuff-vBx760zMwVl1zn0xmxKlDV5Kc_s_J7hmXWsOe3A7IEy4YIgtgLn93o9SoTqi7WCvrzXX8nF6xhY8j5oFYtNBzVMUnDGHVuHcGZY-_g3AVBCV1XgGN8kToSrRHlS7FQZhWD2vgEzUDJ--oeXBFP5QJsk2uOn-nHAvsdR32wQL1WjuFgVI7bKAEcJBMopb7K5r-aUB7GUv-3i1_R0Fl1Ifnb-1lygeVnD8p8jqAofY1MvF8BdZZ2i6jYzPAQSzqNBHAVWSs3MflP2yDV8pU7PM041i8nQtcd-ZQNxg1FVm0ZIwIhofVAzVByfo0s6E__JgAvqJvuUdcXZ15qs1ulSkfLOnw8fIk5B9MtJB4Rg3C2AZr4EkeuO6AR4yZGoiRcQTH1VlXi2EHp1EUdxUc7MX3J1O2bywRub2kkgXtIHtQwnuqXgK2b3A9_PC6eM-l6pgYevaXazJP2VgwLVwywdLd5jewNHZy0KslsOgUqgoUWdE7fyLOp3eRTwgziUByZ3b_72fRd7wiUzLZ_f2_w7SwK9snC11JakpuvE_zHz3sRTEhp4ey1E1gFosrM6E_Nzil1AIwbVKDC7_B2Hs